No offense to anyone here.

1:24:50.085 --> 1:24:52.838
Okay, then. How-- how
about Sojou-- Sojourner?

1:24:53.422 --> 1:24:55.340
[Gloria] Yeah, it sounds
like a travel magazine.

1:24:55.632 --> 1:24:56.967
-As in truth.
-[Gloria] No, I know,

1:24:56.967 --> 1:24:58.385
-I know what you mean.
-Something that reflects

1:24:58.385 --> 1:24:59.469
the
community.

1:24:59.928 --> 1:25:01.430
Wait. How about Ms.?

1:25:05.809 --> 1:25:07.394
Ms. Magazine?

1:25:10.188 --> 1:25:12.232
Some political leaders,
and some others,

1:25:12.232 --> 1:25:15.652
have taken to
not addressing women

1:25:16.486 --> 1:25:18.113
by miss or missus.

1:25:18.739 --> 1:25:23.327
Uh. By-- they've gone
to the miss, M-S.

1:25:24.161 --> 1:25:25.746
Why not do that
with White House letters?

1:25:26.872 --> 1:25:27.914
[chuckles]

1:25:29.166 --> 1:25:31.668
I-- I guess,
I'm a little old-fashioned,

1:25:32.085 --> 1:25:37.799
uh, but, uh, I rather--
rather prefer

1:25:37.799 --> 1:25:39.134
the miss or missus or...

1:25:39.134 --> 1:25:41.553
Well, it's not miss,
it's not missus,

1:25:41.553 --> 1:25:43.764
it's just
none of your goddamn business.

1:25:43.764 --> 1:25:45.474
[Nixon] Yeah, I can assure you
some of the things--

1:25:45.724 --> 1:25:47.225
-Ms.
-Well,

1:25:47.225 --> 1:25:49.478
it does have one big advantage.

1:25:49.895 --> 1:25:52.022
-What?
-It's short.

1:25:52.856 --> 1:25:53.899
[all laugh]

1:26:03.408 --> 1:26:04.910
