1:34:15.859 --> 1:34:17.235
and running for congress.

1:34:17.235 --> 1:34:19.487
Bella Abzug
known as Battling Bella

1:34:19.487 --> 1:34:22.365
is challenging an incumbent
on New York's west side.

1:34:22.365 --> 1:34:24.909
Helping her campaign,
the increasingly visible

1:34:24.909 --> 1:34:27.745
face of the women's movement,
Ms. Gloria Steinem.

1:34:28.746 --> 1:34:30.707
Good job, Bella!

1:34:32.166 --> 1:34:34.836
I wish they loved you that much
in the liberal suburbs.

1:34:34.836 --> 1:34:37.171
[laughs] Why should they?

1:34:38.006 --> 1:34:40.758
I'm everything they moved
to the suburbs to escape,

1:34:41.092 --> 1:34:43.761
the daughter of a Jewish butcher
from the Bronx.

1:34:44.304 --> 1:34:46.556
I've got to convince them
that-- that this girl

1:34:46.556 --> 1:34:47.807
who worked at her father's

1:34:47.807 --> 1:34:50.226
Live and Let Live
butcher shop is a step up.

1:34:50.602 --> 1:34:52.604
Well, we're gonna go
to all the places that people

1:34:52.604 --> 1:34:54.522
-don't usually campaign.
-Okay.

1:34:59.611 --> 1:35:02.238
You need Bella Abzug
as your congressperson.

1:35:02.238 --> 1:35:04.699
Nineteenth District,
Greenwich Village,

1:35:04.699 --> 1:35:05.992
lower east side.

1:35:06.451 --> 1:35:08.494
It's the greatest things of all,
is the sense of injustice

1:35:08.494 --> 1:35:10.204
and you've got that
and I think that's fantastic.

1:35:10.496 --> 1:35:12.540
Most people in the mid-west,
they don't have that.

1:35:12.540 --> 1:35:14.000
-Oh, call me Bella.
-Hi.

1:35:14.000 --> 1:35:15.501
Nice to see you.
Don't forget to vote.

1:35:15.501 --> 1:35:16.544
-Oh, no.
-[laughs]

1:35:16.544 --> 1:35:18.254
-You want a pretzel?
-Oh, of course.

1:35:18.963 --> 1:35:20.924
You see-- you see, Gloria,

1:35:20.924 --> 1:35:23.051
it's not enough just for me
to get elected.

1:35:23.051 --> 1:35:25.053
We need women of all colors
and stripes

1:35:25.053 --> 1:35:26.387
on both sides of the aisle.

1:35:26.721 --> 1:35:29.641
I mean, we don't want to replace
a white male middle class elite

1:35:29.641 --> 1:35:31.601
with a white female
middle class elite.

1:35:31.601 --> 1:35:33.478
No offense to Betty Friedan.

1:35:37.190 --> 1:35:41.194
-[indistinct chatter]
-[typewriter keys clacking]

1:35:41.736 --> 1:35:42.904
[Bella] Betty's pissed.

1:35:45.031 --> 1:35:46.449
-Why?
-Because the media

1:35:46.449 --> 1:35:48.409
is calling you
the face of feminism

1:35:48.409 --> 1:35:50.119
and her the mother
of the movement.

1:35:50.119 --> 1:35:51.287
It makes her feel done.

1:35:52.080 --> 1:35:53.998
You haven't read what she's been
saying about you?

1:35:53.998 --> 1:35:55.333
-Hmm.
-No. I haven't read any of it.

1:35:55.333 --> 1:35:56.876
-Why?
-"The disruptors of the women's

1:35:56.876 --> 1:35:59.420
movement are the ones
trying to push lesbianism

1:35:59.420 --> 1:36:00.672
or hatred of men

1:36:00.672 --> 1:36:02.757
-onto the movement."
-Okay. Okay. Stop it.

1:36:03.007 --> 1:36:04.258
She thinks you're profiteering

1:36:04.258 --> 1:36:05.885
off the movement
with Ms. magazines.

1:36:05.885 --> 1:36:07.762
As if this magazine
will ever turn profit.

1:36:07.762 --> 1:36:10.014
You need to respond
to her in public.

1:36:10.014 --> 1:36:11.641
No, I won't respond.

1:36:11.641 --> 1:36:15.186
I-- I refuse to feed the idea
that women can't get along.

1:36:15.186 --> 1:36:18.064
Sometimes we don't get along.
We argue. We fight.

1:36:18.606 --> 1:36:21.985
And that reminds me, I came here
to tell you in person

1:36:21.985 --> 1:36:24.487
you have been elected
in absentia to represent

1:36:24.487 --> 1:36:25.989
the National Women's
Political Caucus

1:36:26.280 --> 1:36:29.826
-at the Democratic Convention.
-No. No, no, no.

1:36:29.826 --> 1:36:31.536
Betty was actually the ad
campaign that'd be elected

1:36:31.536 --> 1:36:32.745
-and she lost.
-[Gloria] I don't want

1:36:32.745 --> 1:36:34.288
-that job, Bella.
-[cupboard closes]

1:36:34.288 --> 1:36:35.331
That's-- that's why I didn't go.

1:36:35.623 --> 1:36:37.583
That is exactly why
you should have that job.

1:36:37.583 --> 1:36:40.253
And exactly how does
that make sense?

1:36:40.503 --> 1:36:43.798
A reluctant spokeswoman is more
likely to represent the group.

1:36:43.798 --> 1:36:46.467
I have no desire to make
an enemy out of Betty Friedan.

1:36:47.301 --> 1:36:48.344
Too late.

1:36:49.429 --> 1:36:51.264
If you avoid conflict,
my darling,

1:36:51.848 --> 1:36:53.516
conflict will seek you out.

1:36:54.642 --> 1:36:56.144
One may be amused this year...

1:36:56.144 --> 1:36:58.646
the Democratic National
Convention here in Miami,

1:36:58.646 --> 1:37:00.982
by the high-octave span
of women's voices

1:37:01.441 --> 1:37:03.359
gathered together
at the derelict

1:37:03.359 --> 1:37:05.028
Betsy Ross Hotel,

1:37:05.028 --> 1:37:07.030
headquarters
of the recently formed

1:37:07.030 --> 1:37:08.823
National Women's
Political Caucus.

1:37:09.282 --> 1:37:10.533
[telephone ringing]

1:37:10.533 --> 1:37:11.909
[reporter continues]
One might be amused

1:37:11.909 --> 1:37:13.953
by the rooms
with unmade beds,

1:37:13.953 --> 1:37:16.706
yogurt cartons, chests covered
with blue jeans and bras,

1:37:16.998 --> 1:37:18.458
but only briefly.

1:37:18.458 --> 1:37:20.418
Betsy Ross Hotel
is a power set.

1:37:20.793 --> 1:37:22.503
More than a third
of the delegates

1:37:22.503 --> 1:37:23.629
this year are women.

1:37:23.921 --> 1:37:26.340
There's a strong women's plank
in the platform.

1:37:26.716 --> 1:37:27.717
Four years ago, there was none.

1:37:27.717 --> 1:37:28.593
[telephone ringing]

1:37:29.343 --> 1:37:32.013
Can they do it or will they be
torn apart by internal strife?

1:37:33.765 --> 1:37:36.059
-[indistinct chatter]
-What a day.

1:37:36.059 --> 1:37:37.852
[Bella] Can you put the rest
of these in the packet?

1:37:37.852 --> 1:37:39.145
There should be four pages each.

1:37:39.145 --> 1:37:41.105
What the hell
did Betty do today?

1:37:41.105 --> 1:37:42.857
Well, threatened to call
a press conference

1:37:42.857 --> 1:37:44.400
and expose the caucus.

1:37:45.985 --> 1:37:47.487
Same as she does every day.

1:37:49.781 --> 1:37:51.491
-[sighs]
-[telephone ringing]

1:37:51.741 --> 1:37:52.992
You know why Betty
doesn't yell at me?

1:37:53.451 --> 1:37:55.995
-Why?
-Because I yell back louder!

1:37:56.579 --> 1:37:58.414
[all laugh]

1:37:58.873 --> 1:38:00.208
Oh, eat your beer nuts.

1:38:01.000 --> 1:38:02.335
Look, we didn't get
all our planks,

1:38:02.752 --> 1:38:04.045
but we will in Houston.

1:38:04.587 --> 1:38:05.963
You're working from within
the movement now.

1:38:06.339 --> 1:38:08.007
Change comes from within.

1:38:08.424 --> 1:38:09.592
[telephone ringing]

1:38:10.009 --> 1:38:11.969
[woman] They want you
for the cover of Newsweek.

1:38:11.969 --> 1:38:13.930
I won't do a cover photograph.

1:38:13.930 --> 1:38:17.475
Yeah. A movement is lots
and lots of people moving.

1:38:17.475 --> 1:38:20.103
Not one person
being photographed.

1:38:20.103 --> 1:38:23.189
Not one white woman. Not me.

1:38:23.898 --> 1:38:25.566
There would be a movement
without me.

1:38:26.692 --> 1:38:29.487
They won't do the story
unless you pose for the cover.

1:38:29.821 --> 1:38:31.531
[sighs] I won't do it.

1:38:32.657 --> 1:38:34.992
If they want us
to become the radicals,

1:38:34.992 --> 1:38:39.497
that they fear we are,
then let them stop the ERA

1:38:40.081 --> 1:38:43.292
and we will become
those radicals.

1:38:43.668 --> 1:38:45.419
[crowd cheers]

1:38:46.754 --> 1:38:52.051
This is no simple reform.
It really is a revolution.

1:38:52.593 --> 1:38:56.180
-[crowd cheer]
-[camera shutter clicks]

1:39:02.687 --> 1:39:05.648
Introducing my lovely
young assistant, Gloria.

1:39:06.607 --> 1:39:07.567
Hold still.

1:39:09.652 --> 1:39:11.612
[audience gasps]

1:39:16.826 --> 1:39:19.120
-[audience clapping]
-[woman] Come on, Gloria.

1:39:19.120 --> 1:39:22.248
This isn't the first time you've
had knives thrown at you, is it?

1:39:22.248 --> 1:39:24.584
Yeah. It was one thing to have
a magician in east 'Ledo

1:39:24.584 --> 1:39:26.669
throw knives at you
when you're being paid for it.

1:39:26.669 --> 1:39:28.713
You know, and anyway those
knives were dull.

1:39:28.713 --> 1:39:30.423
And it's-- it's another thing
to have this...

1:39:30.423 --> 1:39:32.049
Oh, let me see that thing.

1:39:32.049 --> 1:39:33.634
Wait, my glasses.

1:39:35.887 --> 1:39:37.388
Oh, I don't really need

1:39:37.388 --> 1:39:39.265
-my glasses. [laughs]
-[laughs]

1:39:39.265 --> 1:39:41.392
Pin the cock on the feminist.

1:39:43.352 --> 1:39:44.812
Ah. Let them be idiots.

1:39:45.062 --> 1:39:47.565
You know, the purpose
of an ass kicking isn't that

1:39:47.565 --> 1:39:49.192
you get your ass kicked
at the right time

1:39:49.192 --> 1:39:52.278
or for the right reason,
it's to keep your ass sensitive.

1:39:52.278 --> 1:39:56.365
It's in full, you know,
detail and it has my hair,

1:39:56.365 --> 1:39:59.368
-and my glasses.
-Yeah. And my labia.

1:39:59.869 --> 1:40:03.664
-[Flo] Yeah.
-[all laugh]

1:40:04.624 --> 1:40:08.502
[crowd] Two, four, six, eight,
ratify in every state....

1:40:08.502 --> 1:40:10.880
[news reporter] The women
here represent the thousands

1:40:10.880 --> 1:40:14.050
who formed the long line
of runners from Seneca Falls

1:40:14.050 --> 1:40:15.676
officially opening the first

1:40:15.676 --> 1:40:17.970
government sponsored convention
on women's rights.

1:40:17.970 --> 1:40:19.180
[news reporter 2]
Gloria Steinem, now

1:40:19.180 --> 1:40:20.223
that the conference
is about to begin,

1:40:20.514 --> 1:40:22.016
-how do you feel?
-Well, I can't tell you

1:40:22.016 --> 1:40:25.019
how thrilling it is to finally
see this miracle happen.

1:40:25.019 --> 1:40:26.938
-I mean, I've never seen--
-[chants]

1:40:26.938 --> 1:40:29.440
None of us have ever seen
women pull off

1:40:29.732 --> 1:40:32.485
such a massive
nationwide two-year process

1:40:32.485 --> 1:40:35.154
culminating in what is probably
the most racially,

1:40:35.154 --> 1:40:38.199
economically, and geographically
representative body

1:40:38.199 --> 1:40:40.201
that this nation has ever seen.

1:40:40.201 --> 1:40:44.330
So, the bar is very high.
We have a lot to accomplish.

1:40:44.330 --> 1:40:46.958
[indistinct chatter]

1:40:48.501 --> 1:40:50.670
[Bella exclaims, chuckles]
Oh, my knees.

1:40:50.920 --> 1:40:52.421
Bella, how the hell are we gonna

1:40:52.421 --> 1:40:54.090
-get 2,000 delegates to agree...
-[pants]

1:40:54.090 --> 1:40:56.842
..on 26 multi issue planks
in three days?

1:40:56.842 --> 1:40:59.929
By arguing, and voting,
by not shutting up.

1:40:59.929 --> 1:41:01.847
It's called democracy.

1:41:02.098 --> 1:41:06.727
Oh, the Girl Scouts.
God, I love a pageant. [laughs]

1:41:07.061 --> 1:41:07.979
Stop the bus.

1:41:08.521 --> 1:41:11.107
This is going to be a disaster.
Stop the bus

1:41:11.107 --> 1:41:15.611
-now!
-[crowd] Now ERA! Now ERA now!

1:41:15.611 --> 1:41:18.239
[crowd cheering]

1:41:26.289 --> 1:41:31.002
Women are human.
We are united on that.

1:41:33.296 --> 1:41:38.926
No one person and no subgroup
at this conference

1:41:38.926 --> 1:41:42.096
has the right answer.

1:41:42.805 --> 1:41:45.599
Wonder Woman
is not a delegate here.

1:41:45.891 --> 1:41:47.685
[crowd cheering]

1:41:48.561 --> 1:41:50.813
We will not be brainwashed

1:41:51.063 --> 1:41:55.776
by those who predict chaos
and failure for us.

1:41:56.235 --> 1:41:59.864
Tell them they lie and move on.

1:41:59.864 --> 1:42:02.742
[crowd cheering]

1:42:03.534 --> 1:42:04.827
The cause...

1:42:05.661 --> 1:42:09.790
the cause of equal
and human rights...

1:42:10.916 --> 1:42:13.586
will reap what is sown.

1:42:14.920 --> 1:42:19.508
November 18 through November 21,

1:42:20.134 --> 1:42:23.846
1977.

1:42:25.222 --> 1:42:26.599
What will you reap?

1:42:28.434 --> 1:42:30.227
What will you sow?

1:42:30.728 --> 1:42:33.689
[crowd cheering]

1:42:38.152 --> 1:42:44.116
This gavel was used by
Susan B. Anthony in 1896.

1:42:47.078 --> 1:42:50.748
Bella Abzug,
may you preside with the truth

1:42:50.748 --> 1:42:53.834
of what this gavel means
to American women

1:42:53.834 --> 1:42:56.587
who are again on the move.

1:42:57.046 --> 1:42:59.548
[crowd cheering]

1:43:07.181 --> 1:43:08.349
The women's movement...

1:43:09.225 --> 1:43:12.103
has become an indestructible
part of American life.

1:43:13.521 --> 1:43:16.941
It is the homemaker
deciding that raising children,

1:43:17.274 --> 1:43:19.443
cooking, and cleaning,
and all the other things

1:43:19.443 --> 1:43:23.864
she does for her family, should
be accorded value and respect.

1:43:24.949 --> 1:43:27.368
It is the young woman student

1:43:27.368 --> 1:43:29.453
deciding that she wants
to play baseball,

1:43:29.870 --> 1:43:34.208
carry a torch, major in physics,
or become a brain surgeon.

1:43:34.750 --> 1:43:36.752
-It is the working woman...
-[crowd clapping]

1:43:36.752 --> 1:43:38.587
...demanding equal pay.

1:43:39.380 --> 1:43:40.965
It is the divorced woman,

1:43:41.715 --> 1:43:45.177
fighting for social security
benefits in her own right.

1:43:45.761 --> 1:43:49.056
It is the mother organizing
a daycare center.

1:43:49.056 --> 1:43:51.559
It is the battered wife
seeking help.

1:43:51.809 --> 1:43:54.145
It is the woman running
for public office.

1:43:55.229 --> 1:43:57.273
It is the woman on welfare

1:43:57.273 --> 1:44:00.025
looking for a decent part
of American life.

1:44:00.317 --> 1:44:02.319
Let this conference
be the beginning

1:44:02.319 --> 1:44:04.071
of making our democracy

1:44:04.071 --> 1:44:07.116
what it should have been
200 years ago!

1:44:10.911 --> 1:44:12.037
[news reporter]
Seven miles south

1:44:12.371 --> 1:44:14.165
from the National
Women's Conference in Houston,

1:44:14.165 --> 1:44:16.917
a protest, spearheaded
by Phyllis Schlafly,

1:44:17.168 --> 1:44:19.128
calls itself
the pro-family rally

1:44:19.462 --> 1:44:21.213
opposed
to the Equal Rights Amendment.

1:44:21.464 --> 1:44:24.425
I'm very proud
that they excluded me

1:44:24.425 --> 1:44:25.885
from that convention

1:44:25.885 --> 1:44:29.763
and I'm here where we're
not ashamed and not afraid

1:44:30.139 --> 1:44:34.477
to ask God's blessing on this
crowd assembled here today.

1:44:36.896 --> 1:44:40.149
-Oh, my God. That's Dolores.
-Huerta, Right.

1:44:40.691 --> 1:44:42.818
She said she'd be coming
to Houston with the contention

1:44:42.818 --> 1:44:45.404
of female farm workers,
to protest abortion.

1:44:45.404 --> 1:44:46.697
-[Robert] I watched...
-Yeah, well, she has

1:44:46.697 --> 1:44:48.073
-a lot of kids.
-Ten.

1:44:48.073 --> 1:44:49.241
...of young people

1:44:49.241 --> 1:44:51.160
and the greatest tragedy
of all

1:44:51.827 --> 1:44:56.123
...was to see three former
first ladies of this nation,

1:44:56.123 --> 1:44:58.876
excuse me,
two former first ladies

1:44:59.126 --> 1:45:00.294
and the current wife

1:45:00.294 --> 1:45:02.254
of the president
of the United States

1:45:02.713 --> 1:45:04.965
standing by their very presence

1:45:05.216 --> 1:45:09.929
alongside of Abzug
approving of sexual perversion

1:45:09.929 --> 1:45:12.890
and the murder of young people
in their mother's womb.

1:45:12.890 --> 1:45:14.767
-[crowd clamoring]
-What a disgrace!

1:45:15.226 --> 1:45:17.436
Excuse me.
Can we turn this shit off?

1:45:23.859 --> 1:45:24.818
[door closes]

1:45:38.332 --> 1:45:39.667
[toilet flushes]

1:45:40.167 --> 1:45:44.672
[indistinct chatter]

1:45:47.758 --> 1:45:49.677
[woman] It's different
than all of them, you know.

1:45:50.135 --> 1:45:51.512
Excuse me. I'm--
I'm sorry to bother you.

1:45:51.512 --> 1:45:52.846
Did you not get
a room assignment?

1:45:53.097 --> 1:45:54.265
No. But this is fine.

1:45:54.265 --> 1:45:56.016
Well, is there anything
you need?

1:45:56.767 --> 1:45:58.852
We could use someone
to take notes actually.

1:45:58.852 --> 1:46:00.563
Well, that's why I'm here.

1:46:01.188 --> 1:46:02.189
Thank you.

1:46:02.523 --> 1:46:04.483
-Wilma Mankiller.
-Gloria Steinem.

1:46:04.733 --> 1:46:07.903
We need to make it clear that
while other women here gathered

1:46:07.903 --> 1:46:10.698
are fighting for equality
inside the mainstream,

1:46:10.698 --> 1:46:13.284
we native women are fighting
for tribal sovereignty.

1:46:13.826 --> 1:46:17.037
We're fighting for our entire
culture outside the mainstream.

1:46:17.663 --> 1:46:18.747
So, chime in.

1:46:19.290 --> 1:46:22.334
Let's draw up a list
of our most critical issues.

1:46:23.669 --> 1:46:25.629
What about the loss
of our tribal languages?

1:46:26.213 --> 1:46:28.382
We're not even allowed
to teach it in our schools.

1:46:28.966 --> 1:46:32.094
Our language is the very heart
of who we are as a people.

1:46:32.636 --> 1:46:36.765
And if that disappears,
that's it. It's gone forever.

1:46:37.641 --> 1:46:39.059
[women agreeing]

1:46:39.560 --> 1:46:41.020
[indistinct chatter]

1:46:41.020 --> 1:46:42.605
-Gloria.
-Dolores?

1:46:42.605 --> 1:46:43.814
They told me I'd find you

1:46:43.814 --> 1:46:45.608
in one of these hallways
running ragged.

1:46:45.608 --> 1:46:47.568
I thought you're across town,
are you okay?

1:46:47.568 --> 1:46:50.070
Do you have a minute?
I'm just...

1:46:50.487 --> 1:46:52.281
Yes. Yeah. Of course.

1:46:52.281 --> 1:46:53.949
One of these rooms
has gotta be empty.

1:46:53.949 --> 1:46:54.825
All right.

1:46:55.326 --> 1:46:57.036
We've got to have some
very specific resolutions

1:46:57.036 --> 1:46:59.830
for Asian-American women
on sweatshops--

1:47:00.456 --> 1:47:02.207
Oh, Gloria.
We could use a writer.

1:47:02.708 --> 1:47:04.376
I'll be back in a minute. Sorry.

1:47:06.629 --> 1:47:09.173
I promise to be a scribe
for the minority caucuses.

1:47:09.173 --> 1:47:10.883
-I should go now.
-No, no, no, no. Come here.

1:47:11.175 --> 1:47:13.594
-[indistinct chatter]
-Excuse me.

1:47:25.189 --> 1:47:26.940
You know, I'm a devout Catholic.

1:47:27.900 --> 1:47:29.401
You know, along with Cesar,

1:47:29.902 --> 1:47:32.237
I've been anti-abortion
my entire life.

1:47:33.614 --> 1:47:35.324
I'm here with
my fellow farm workers

1:47:35.324 --> 1:47:37.785
to demonstrate in support
of the Right to Lifers, but...

1:47:40.537 --> 1:47:43.040
I looked at the faces
in that angry crowd...

1:47:44.792 --> 1:47:46.418
and I saw some
of the same people

1:47:46.418 --> 1:47:48.337
who fight our unions,
and hate our cause,

1:47:48.337 --> 1:47:50.589
extreme right-wingers,
even the clan and...

1:47:52.299 --> 1:47:53.384
I had to get out.

1:47:53.926 --> 1:47:55.678
Hmm. Dolores, you know...

1:47:56.512 --> 1:47:58.722
no one in their--
in their right mind

1:47:58.722 --> 1:48:00.391
is-- is pro-abortion.

1:48:01.100 --> 1:48:02.935
Nobody gets up in the morning
and says,

1:48:03.477 --> 1:48:05.396
"Great. I'm gonna have
a procedure today." It's...

1:48:06.355 --> 1:48:08.148
it is the method
of the last resort.

1:48:10.275 --> 1:48:13.737
But reproductive freedom and--
and the right to choose

1:48:13.737 --> 1:48:15.364
belongs to the woman, right?

1:48:16.198 --> 1:48:17.241
I mean, that's...

1:48:18.158 --> 1:48:20.619
that's what being pro-choice
is-- is all about.

1:48:23.288 --> 1:48:24.748
I have ten kids.

1:48:25.999 --> 1:48:28.544
And I love each and every one
of them dearly, but...

1:48:28.544 --> 1:48:30.629
...but it's been hard.

1:48:32.589 --> 1:48:34.174
We don't wanna go
against the church...

1:48:35.968 --> 1:48:37.636
but we have to think
of ourselves first.

1:48:38.762 --> 1:48:40.305
All these people who have
an issue

1:48:40.305 --> 1:48:41.348
with having an abortion, well,

1:48:41.348 --> 1:48:42.850
what are they doing
for the children

1:48:42.850 --> 1:48:43.851
once they are born?

1:48:44.852 --> 1:48:45.978
Even the church.

1:48:47.312 --> 1:48:50.023
What's the church doing
to help us raise our children?

1:48:50.858 --> 1:48:52.317
Are they providing
infant centers?

1:48:52.317 --> 1:48:54.194
Are they providing resources
for our teenagers--

1:48:54.194 --> 1:48:55.571
Dolores, come with me tomorrow.

1:48:55.571 --> 1:48:56.864
It's the last day
of the conference

1:48:56.864 --> 1:48:58.365
and-- and I want you there.

1:48:59.199 --> 1:49:01.452
The president and congress...

1:49:01.452 --> 1:49:05.080
should provide
for full quality education.

1:49:05.456 --> 1:49:09.793
And for the full implementation
and enforcement

1:49:09.793 --> 1:49:11.545
of all affirmative

1:49:11.545 --> 1:49:13.464
-action programs...
-[crowd cheering]

1:49:13.464 --> 1:49:17.301
Deportation of mothers
of American born children

1:49:17.301 --> 1:49:18.469
must be stopped,

1:49:18.927 --> 1:49:21.930
and legislation enacted
for parents

1:49:22.264 --> 1:49:23.974
to remain with their children.

1:49:23.974 --> 1:49:25.559
Would all those in favor

1:49:25.559 --> 1:49:28.645
of the sexual preference
resolution, please rise.

1:49:28.645 --> 1:49:29.688
[crowd cheering]

1:49:30.814 --> 1:49:34.109
[woman]
Be seated. Please stay in order.

1:49:34.401 --> 1:49:37.446
All those opposed to
this resolution, please rise.

1:49:37.946 --> 1:49:40.783
The resolution has clearly
carried and is adopted.

1:49:40.783 --> 1:49:42.576
[crowd cheering]

1:49:42.576 --> 1:49:46.455
The federal government should
guarantee tribal rights...

1:49:46.872 --> 1:49:50.626
Asian-Pacific American women
are wrongly thought to be...

1:49:50.626 --> 1:49:52.461
[woman]
The current system of insurance

1:49:52.711 --> 1:49:55.547
is one where women pay more
and get less.

1:49:55.798 --> 1:49:58.842
...of covering homemakers
and their own rights...

1:49:58.842 --> 1:50:01.595
We would like to substitute that
as follows, Madam Chairperson...

1:50:01.595 --> 1:50:04.014
[woman] And your time
has expired. Sit down.

1:50:04.014 --> 1:50:07.351
[Bella] I move the adoption
of the following resolution.

1:50:07.351 --> 1:50:09.895
The Equal Rights Amendment
should be ratified.

1:50:09.895 --> 1:50:12.648
All those in favor,
will you please rise?

1:50:14.107 --> 1:50:16.652
-[gavel bangs]
-The resolution has passed.

1:50:16.652 --> 1:50:18.111
[crowd cheering]

1:50:25.327 --> 1:50:27.955
[vocalizing]

1:50:28.455 --> 1:50:32.668
[crowd singing]
♪ I do believe ♪

1:50:33.252 --> 1:50:39.258
♪ We shall overcome someday ♪

1:50:51.520 --> 1:50:52.896
[Wilma] Gloria.

1:50:54.606 --> 1:50:56.275
Thank you for standing
beside us.

1:50:56.942 --> 1:50:59.611
You wear this and remember
we're also standing beside you.

1:51:00.779 --> 1:51:01.780
Thank you.

1:51:03.240 --> 1:51:04.449
And you can wear this...

1:51:05.367 --> 1:51:07.995
when we get you out there
dancing at our powwows.

1:51:09.079 --> 1:51:10.205
-And we will.
-[Gloria chuckles]

1:51:11.164 --> 1:51:12.416
So did it pass?

1:51:13.417 --> 1:51:15.502
-What?
-The ERA.

1:51:16.795 --> 1:51:19.715
Of course.
They voted, didn't they?

1:51:19.715 --> 1:51:22.384
I mean, more people stood up
for it than against it.

1:51:23.552 --> 1:51:25.637
Yeah. But did it pass?

1:51:28.807 --> 1:51:29.933
I don't think so.

1:51:29.933 --> 1:51:31.393
[child exclaiming]

1:51:32.019 --> 1:51:34.813
-[dog barking]
-[indistinct chatter]

1:51:38.567 --> 1:51:40.694
-[man] Yeah. Let's proceed.
-[speaking foreign language]

1:51:41.987 --> 1:51:43.947
[Charlie] It's going to be
an uphill battle.

1:51:43.947 --> 1:51:46.700
There's never been an elected
female Cherokee chief before.

1:51:47.034 --> 1:51:48.160
[Gloria] There will be now.

1:51:48.994 --> 1:51:50.203
Campaign's been tough.

1:51:50.954 --> 1:51:53.290
We've had our car torched,
death threats.

1:51:54.541 --> 1:51:57.252
Wilma just pushes on.
Nothing stops her.

1:51:57.711 --> 1:51:58.670
No fear.

1:51:59.046 --> 1:52:01.798
Well, she's lucky
to have you beside her.

1:52:03.634 --> 1:52:05.844
[Wilma] Hello.
[speaking foreign language]

1:52:06.678 --> 1:52:07.846
Good to see you.

1:52:07.846 --> 1:52:08.847
[Charlie] No, I'm the lucky one.

1:52:08.847 --> 1:52:10.474
[man] How are you?
Thank you.

1:52:10.891 --> 1:52:12.643
So, how did you two
get together?

1:52:13.352 --> 1:52:16.605
When I met Wilma ten years ago,
she was definitely on her own.

1:52:18.482 --> 1:52:20.400
Well, after working together
for a couple of years

1:52:20.400 --> 1:52:21.568
on a water project,

1:52:22.486 --> 1:52:24.321
I started to say, "You know,

1:52:24.655 --> 1:52:27.366
I can tell there's electricity
going on between us."

1:52:27.950 --> 1:52:29.868
And so I asked her. I said,

1:52:29.868 --> 1:52:32.412
"Uh. Wilma, you want to go
see a movie?

1:52:33.747 --> 1:52:35.248
-You want to go see Rambo?"
-[laughs]

1:52:36.124 --> 1:52:39.336
She said "Rambo?
I hate Rambo."

1:52:40.253 --> 1:52:41.296
I thought, "Oops."

1:52:41.672 --> 1:52:43.090
And so I drove to Tulsa

1:52:43.090 --> 1:52:45.300
and pulled in
at a Coney Island hot dog place.

1:52:45.884 --> 1:52:47.719
She said,
"What are we doing here?"

1:52:48.178 --> 1:52:49.388
I said, "We're here to eat."

1:52:50.013 --> 1:52:52.265
She said, "Here?"
I said, "Yeah."

1:52:54.810 --> 1:52:58.313
-She said, "I hate hot dogs."
-[laughs]

1:52:58.313 --> 1:52:59.523
I said, "Oh, my God."

1:53:00.190 --> 1:53:03.735
I struck out here.
I mean I love those hot dogs.

1:53:04.194 --> 1:53:05.278
Dang.

1:53:06.113 --> 1:53:08.740
We live in a country
where our contributions

1:53:08.740 --> 1:53:10.909
to democracy
have been overlooked.

1:53:10.909 --> 1:53:12.327
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

1:53:12.327 --> 1:53:15.455
Benjamin Franklin acknowledged
the Iroquois Confederacy

1:53:15.455 --> 1:53:18.208
was the model for
the Constitutional Convention.

1:53:18.208 --> 1:53:20.419
In fact, he invited
two Iroquois men

1:53:20.419 --> 1:53:21.837
to Philadelphia as advisers.

1:53:22.879 --> 1:53:24.423
-[rain pattering]
-Their first question...

1:53:24.423 --> 1:53:26.550
-[indistinct chatter]
-..."Where are the women?"

1:53:28.176 --> 1:53:30.595
Now, we Cherokee,
we consult our women elders

1:53:30.595 --> 1:53:34.016
on every important decision,
but we've never had a woman

1:53:34.266 --> 1:53:35.976
as a democratically
elected chief.

1:53:35.976 --> 1:53:37.561
Let's change that this year.

1:53:37.561 --> 1:53:38.937
[people cheering]

1:53:40.731 --> 1:53:42.357
Vote Mankiller.

1:53:42.357 --> 1:53:43.859
How'd you get the name
Mankiller?

1:53:45.694 --> 1:53:47.863
-I earned it.
-[people laugh]

1:53:47.863 --> 1:53:51.324
-You earned it.
-[chuckles]

1:53:51.324 --> 1:53:52.451
Okay.

1:53:53.160 --> 1:53:54.411
It's an inherited title
that means

1:53:54.411 --> 1:53:56.246
-protector of the village.
-Oh.

1:53:57.247 --> 1:53:58.832
Used to be Whiteman Killer.

1:53:59.666 --> 1:54:01.293
[laughs]

1:54:03.712 --> 1:54:05.964
-Hmm. You know...
-[sighs]

1:54:06.923 --> 1:54:09.509
...I read that
the Cherokee nation

1:54:09.509 --> 1:54:11.094
was once matrilineal,
is that true?

1:54:11.470 --> 1:54:12.512
Yes. Once.

1:54:14.431 --> 1:54:16.433
And the sun is female
and the moon is male.

1:54:16.433 --> 1:54:17.434
What?

1:54:18.310 --> 1:54:20.228
See, the sun is always there.

1:54:21.396 --> 1:54:23.023
The moon comes and goes.

1:54:24.483 --> 1:54:27.319
[both laugh]

1:54:29.279 --> 1:54:31.531
This is an extraordinary place.

1:54:31.531 --> 1:54:34.701
Your home, you know,
with all its family and friends.

1:54:35.786 --> 1:54:37.329
I've been here most of my life.

1:54:40.082 --> 1:54:41.208
Do you ever go home, Gloria?

1:54:41.208 --> 1:54:43.627
Oh, you mean my apartment
in New York?

1:54:43.627 --> 1:54:46.046
I think the-- the longest
I've been there

1:54:46.046 --> 1:54:47.714
in the last year
has been eight days.

1:54:52.677 --> 1:54:53.845
The ballots are in.

1:54:56.890 --> 1:54:58.141
[speaking foreign language]

1:54:59.601 --> 1:55:01.019
-Oh.
-Chief?

1:55:01.603 --> 1:55:02.604
Yes.

1:55:03.230 --> 1:55:06.108
-[both laugh]
-We did it. We did it.

1:55:09.569 --> 1:55:12.322
[people clamoring]

1:55:13.073 --> 1:55:14.157
Go home murderer.

1:55:15.450 --> 1:55:16.326
Go home!

1:55:16.660 --> 1:55:18.036
[man over speaker]
In the name of Jesus!

1:55:18.036 --> 1:55:21.164
we must protect
the sacred life of the unborn.

1:55:21.832 --> 1:55:24.876
[indistinct chatter]

1:55:27.838 --> 1:55:28.839
Murderers!

1:55:34.052 --> 1:55:36.513
Baby killer,
that's what you are!

1:55:47.649 --> 1:55:49.943
[crowd clamoring]

1:56:08.170 --> 1:56:11.882
[priest] Today, I've invited
a very special guest

1:56:12.465 --> 1:56:13.758
to give our homily.

1:56:14.342 --> 1:56:16.011
Glory be to God.

1:56:17.971 --> 1:56:19.931
-For Gloria.
-[people laugh]

1:56:24.769 --> 1:56:26.646
You may be surprised
to see me here.

1:56:27.564 --> 1:56:29.107
I-- I'm surprised, too.

1:56:30.567 --> 1:56:33.570
Original culture saw
the presence of God

1:56:33.570 --> 1:56:35.530
in all living things...

1:56:36.406 --> 1:56:38.200
-including women.
-[man clears throat]

1:56:38.491 --> 1:56:42.037
Only in the last 500
to 5,000 years,

1:56:42.037 --> 1:56:43.455
depending on where you lived,

1:56:43.747 --> 1:56:46.708
has godliness been withdrawn
from nature,

1:56:47.167 --> 1:56:50.754
from females and from
particular races of men, right?

1:56:51.463 --> 1:56:56.718
Though patriarchal culture
made hierarchy seem inevitable.

1:56:57.802 --> 1:56:59.262
For 95 percent of history,

1:56:59.262 --> 1:57:02.349
humans have been
more likely to see

1:57:02.349 --> 1:57:05.810
the circle as our natural
paradigm.

1:57:05.810 --> 1:57:08.563
And millions still do
from Native Americans here

1:57:09.189 --> 1:57:12.108
to original cultures
around the world.

1:57:13.109 --> 1:57:16.363
When God is depicted
only as a white man...

1:57:17.364 --> 1:57:19.991
and Jesus has blonde hair
and blue eyes

1:57:19.991 --> 1:57:21.159
in the middle
of the Middle East,

1:57:21.159 --> 1:57:22.202
I never understood that.
[laughs]

1:57:22.202 --> 1:57:23.161
[people laughs]

1:57:23.161 --> 1:57:24.996
Then only white men seem godly.

1:57:25.997 --> 1:57:27.958
Priests dressed in skirts

1:57:28.333 --> 1:57:30.710
try to trump
women's birth giving power

1:57:30.710 --> 1:57:34.089
by baptizing
with imitation birth fluid

1:57:34.089 --> 1:57:35.465
and calling us reborn.

1:57:36.007 --> 1:57:39.261
And then going women one better
by promising everlasting life.

1:57:40.720 --> 1:57:43.390
In reality, elaborate concepts
of heaven and hell

1:57:43.848 --> 1:57:48.186
didn't exist before patriarchy.
You just joined your ancestors

1:57:48.478 --> 1:57:52.524
or kept being reincarnated
till you learned enough.

1:57:52.857 --> 1:57:53.984
[all laugh]

1:57:55.277 --> 1:57:58.488
The simple right
to reproductive freedom,

1:57:59.322 --> 1:58:01.658
to sexuality as an expression

1:58:02.158 --> 1:58:04.953
that is separable
to reproduction

1:58:04.953 --> 1:58:07.872
is basic to restoring
the balance

1:58:07.872 --> 1:58:09.624
between women and men.

1:58:10.292 --> 1:58:14.587
A balance between humans
and nature.

1:58:26.975 --> 1:58:28.893
[woman] Hi, Gloria.
I'm so excited

1:58:28.893 --> 1:58:31.104
to finally get to talk to you.

1:58:31.104 --> 1:58:33.648
-Oh, well--
-And I'll say it real quick.

1:58:33.648 --> 1:58:35.692
First of all, I really believe

1:58:35.692 --> 1:58:38.111
that your movement
was a total failure

1:58:38.111 --> 1:58:41.072
and I believe you could admit
that wholeheartedly.

1:58:41.656 --> 1:58:44.659
You are one
of the primary causes

1:58:44.659 --> 1:58:47.537
of the downfall
of our beautiful

1:58:47.537 --> 1:58:50.582
American family
and society today.

1:58:51.666 --> 1:58:55.003
A couple questions. I'd like
to know if you're married.

1:58:55.795 --> 1:58:57.547
-No.
-If you have children.

1:58:58.423 --> 1:59:00.759
-No.
-No, you don't.

1:59:01.009 --> 1:59:01.926
Well, let me tell you.

1:59:02.260 --> 1:59:03.511
-You can't get...
-Is that-- Is that bad?

1:59:03.511 --> 1:59:07.974
...advertisers because
your magazine blanks.

1:59:08.683 --> 1:59:11.144
So, you better go out
and get a job

1:59:11.144 --> 1:59:13.396
and don't ever
have children, lady.

1:59:14.647 --> 1:59:17.484
[woman continues] Gloria Steinem
should rot in hell.

1:59:25.033 --> 1:59:26.159
[teenage Gloria]
Do you regret it?

1:59:27.827 --> 1:59:29.204
Not having kids?

1:59:30.830 --> 1:59:34.334
People always ask me that
and I always feel the pressure

1:59:34.334 --> 1:59:35.668
to say yes, but I...

1:59:37.295 --> 1:59:39.756
-I don't, and I-- I never did.
-[chuckles]

1:59:41.466 --> 1:59:43.301
I always assumed I'd have them.

1:59:44.427 --> 1:59:46.638
Well, not everyone
with vocal chords

1:59:46.638 --> 1:59:48.681
is an opera singer,
not every woman

1:59:48.681 --> 1:59:50.600
with a womb is a mother.
[laughs]

1:59:50.600 --> 1:59:52.644
You'd make a terrible opera
singer.

1:59:53.103 --> 1:59:54.938
But a great tap dancer.

1:59:56.064 --> 1:59:57.357
Are we there yet?

2:00:03.947 --> 2:00:06.241
Gloria, what would you say
to women of color

2:00:06.241 --> 2:00:08.701
who don't feel the feminist
movement includes them

2:00:08.952 --> 2:00:09.994
or is about them?

2:00:10.578 --> 2:00:13.581
Well, I wouldn't say anything.
I would-- I would just listen.

2:00:14.416 --> 2:00:16.960
[Gloria] The biggest
indicator of whether

2:00:16.960 --> 2:00:19.379
a country is violent
within itself

2:00:19.379 --> 2:00:23.758
is not-- Is not poverty, is not
lack of natural resources,

2:00:23.758 --> 2:00:28.304
is not religion
or even degree of democracy.

2:00:28.304 --> 2:00:30.765
It's the degree of violence
against females.

2:00:32.058 --> 2:00:34.102
Okay. Here's my best thing
about instinct.

2:00:34.102 --> 2:00:36.688
If it walks like a duck
and it looks like a duck,

2:00:36.688 --> 2:00:37.856
and quacks like a duck

2:00:37.856 --> 2:00:40.567
and you think it's a pig,
it's a pig.

2:00:52.412 --> 2:00:56.541
The truth will set you free,
but first it will piss you off.

2:00:59.836 --> 2:01:02.130
[siren wailing]

2:01:02.589 --> 2:01:04.257
[horns honking]

2:01:10.805 --> 2:01:13.683
[Gloria] I sometimes wonder
if we are crisscrossing

2:01:13.683 --> 2:01:15.477
Leo's ghostly past.

2:01:16.227 --> 2:01:20.106
Entering the same towns,
roadside diners.

2:01:20.940 --> 2:01:22.233
We're so different... [laughs]

2:01:23.902 --> 2:01:26.029
...and yet so much the same.

2:01:55.058 --> 2:01:56.476
[sighs]

2:02:00.438 --> 2:02:01.356
[groans]

2:02:23.127 --> 2:02:24.087
It's me.

2:02:25.463 --> 2:02:27.840
Um. Oh. No. No, I...

2:02:28.758 --> 2:02:30.718
I-- I had no idea.

2:02:32.011 --> 2:02:34.847
I just-- I needed
to hear your voice.

2:02:36.349 --> 2:02:38.601
No. Um, everything's fine.

2:02:38.601 --> 2:02:41.521
I just-- I just got back
early and I...

2:02:42.689 --> 2:02:44.732
And I thought
that if you were free...

2:02:45.358 --> 2:02:47.068
tomorrow then--
that maybe we could...

2:02:50.989 --> 2:02:52.240
Oh. Oh.

2:02:53.408 --> 2:02:55.285
No. I-- I forgot. I, um...

2:02:56.286 --> 2:02:57.245
No.

2:02:58.204 --> 2:02:59.497
Absolutely. I...

2:03:01.499 --> 2:03:04.711
Yeah. Um. And I'll--
and I'll see you on Saturday.

2:03:06.087 --> 2:03:07.088
All right?

2:03:07.630 --> 2:03:09.549
All right. Just go back
to sleep.

2:03:11.801 --> 2:03:12.885
Good night.

2:03:16.389 --> 2:03:17.599
[phone clatters]

2:03:24.939 --> 2:03:27.025
["Give It To Me Baby" playing]

2:03:33.448 --> 2:03:35.033
♪ Give it to me baby ♪

2:03:40.121 --> 2:03:43.791
[crowd singing]

2:03:44.250 --> 2:03:48.796
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

2:03:48.796 --> 2:03:51.716
-Hey.
-[people cheering]

2:03:52.467 --> 2:03:56.846
Welcome to the post 50 free
from feminine bullshit age.

2:03:56.846 --> 2:04:00.141
Free at last, sweet Jesus.
Free at last.

2:04:03.061 --> 2:04:05.855
