2:04:13.237 --> 2:04:15.281
raised quite a bit
earmarked for Ms.

2:04:15.281 --> 2:04:17.200
Gloria, eat your cake.

2:04:17.200 --> 2:04:19.369
Or dance with Stan.
Look, here he comes.

2:04:19.744 --> 2:04:21.079
-Hello.
-Hi.

2:04:21.079 --> 2:04:22.246
How are you?

2:04:23.164 --> 2:04:25.667
[romantic jazz music playing]

2:05:03.663 --> 2:05:05.331
-[host] Happy birthday, Gloria.
-[Gloria] Thank you.

2:05:05.581 --> 2:05:08.000
So, you are still not married.

2:05:08.292 --> 2:05:12.714
Well, um, I've always said that
I-- I can't mate in captivity.

2:05:13.798 --> 2:05:15.883
When I grow up,
I'm going to go to Hollywood...

2:05:16.968 --> 2:05:18.886
and then I'm going to get
married,

2:05:19.387 --> 2:05:20.430
and settle down...

2:05:21.556 --> 2:05:23.307
and have three kids.

2:05:23.808 --> 2:05:24.976
Then a boxer.

2:05:26.602 --> 2:05:28.646
Oh, no. No, no. no.
A-- A Golden Retriever.

2:05:29.856 --> 2:05:32.608
And a house with a huge yard,
and a swimming pool,

2:05:32.608 --> 2:05:35.445
and a basket for basketball
in the driveway.

2:05:37.029 --> 2:05:39.782
And a game room in the basement
with a record player,

2:05:40.408 --> 2:05:41.909
and a ping-pong table, and...

2:05:43.745 --> 2:05:44.996
and a dance floor.

2:05:45.955 --> 2:05:47.498
That's important, you know.

2:05:47.790 --> 2:05:49.542
-And a car.
-Of course.

2:05:49.834 --> 2:05:51.711
A Ford woody station wagon,
my own.

2:05:52.253 --> 2:05:54.046
And my husband,
he can have his own car, too.

2:05:55.214 --> 2:05:57.258
A Cadillac. Convertible.

2:05:59.886 --> 2:06:02.180
No. Well, that--
Maybe that will be my car.

2:06:02.889 --> 2:06:05.183
And what about love?
Will you be in love?

2:06:05.475 --> 2:06:06.934
Well, yes. Of course.

2:06:07.643 --> 2:06:09.520
Forever and ever after.

2:06:10.062 --> 2:06:11.731
Why aren't you married?

2:06:11.731 --> 2:06:15.985
My relationships were measurable
in-- in years, not days.

2:06:15.985 --> 2:06:19.739
I mean, remember, I grew up
in the 1950s, not even the '60s,

2:06:19.739 --> 2:06:22.867
so I would defend the right for
any woman to have sex with a man

2:06:22.867 --> 2:06:24.160
whose name she doesn't know.

2:06:24.160 --> 2:06:28.122
But my own life
has been about little marriages.

2:06:28.706 --> 2:06:30.541
Do you need a man in your life
to be happy?

2:06:31.042 --> 2:06:32.919
Are you talking about sex?
Or what are you talking about?

2:06:32.919 --> 2:06:34.504
Yes. Sex.

2:06:35.046 --> 2:06:37.965
Well, no. Not now actually.

2:06:37.965 --> 2:06:41.344
But in 20 minutes, that may
change. Who knows? I mean...

2:06:43.679 --> 2:06:45.056
Let's keep the cameras rolling.

2:06:45.556 --> 2:06:47.225
[man over TV]
I just wish Gloria

2:06:47.225 --> 2:06:50.353
would find a good chap
and relax.

2:06:50.853 --> 2:06:55.191
Gloria comes on
with that flat Ohio accent...

2:06:55.191 --> 2:06:58.820
...goes on and on
about women's oppression.

2:06:59.362 --> 2:07:02.782
You feel like either kissing
her or hitting her.

2:07:03.032 --> 2:07:04.617
I can't decide which.

2:07:10.706 --> 2:07:12.416
[brake squeals]

2:07:13.376 --> 2:07:15.378
[woman over radio] Make sure
you have the right temperature.

2:07:15.670 --> 2:07:17.338
[man over radio] Because
that slut from the east village

2:07:17.338 --> 2:07:18.673
