2:11:49.151 --> 2:11:51.570
But partners... I like that.

2:11:52.404 --> 2:11:55.407
What can I say?
We loved each other.

2:11:55.407 --> 2:11:57.743
And, uh, we're both in our 60's

2:11:57.743 --> 2:12:01.497
and hardly needed
to be officially married.

2:12:01.497 --> 2:12:02.790
But David needed a green card.

2:12:03.207 --> 2:12:06.210
And, uh, who could turn down
a full Cherokee wedding?

2:12:06.627 --> 2:12:07.628
Attagirl.

2:12:07.962 --> 2:12:09.839
And besides, we-- we changed
the marriage law,

2:12:09.839 --> 2:12:12.007
so I no longer
had to change my name,

2:12:12.258 --> 2:12:15.136
my legal residence,
my credit rating, right?

2:12:15.511 --> 2:12:17.263
Always the romantic.

2:12:58.470 --> 2:12:59.763
-[speaking foreign language]
-Hi.

2:13:05.019 --> 2:13:06.187
[Gloria] How are you?

2:13:06.645 --> 2:13:08.355
Well, you know
what I always say.

2:13:09.106 --> 2:13:10.733
Every day is a good day.

2:13:12.109 --> 2:13:13.736
[Gloria]
I just spoke to your doctor

2:13:13.736 --> 2:13:16.780
and we can park an ambulance
in the yard, just--

2:13:16.780 --> 2:13:19.241
No. No. [groans]

2:13:20.701 --> 2:13:23.037
I wanna die on my own land.

2:13:26.373 --> 2:13:31.462
Gloria, you are an organizer
to the end. [chuckles]

2:13:37.301 --> 2:13:38.344
Thank you, Billy.

2:13:42.389 --> 2:13:43.682
[Wilma]
Are you thinking of David?

2:13:46.310 --> 2:13:48.479
[Gloria] No. No, I wasn't. I...

2:13:50.856 --> 2:13:52.024
I am...

2:13:53.859 --> 2:13:55.694
always remembering
our wedding here.

2:13:57.363 --> 2:14:01.367
We had one glorious year
together then he got ill.

2:14:03.077 --> 2:14:04.620
Oh, and I just
can't get over it.

2:14:05.496 --> 2:14:07.331
Well, you never should.

2:14:10.042 --> 2:14:11.794
When I see him
on the other side,

2:14:11.794 --> 2:14:14.421
I'll give him a giant bear hug
and tell him.

2:14:14.713 --> 2:14:18.801
-[breathes heavily]
-[wheezes]

2:14:20.719 --> 2:14:22.263
What can I do for you?

2:14:23.222 --> 2:14:25.057
For once there's nothing to do.

2:14:26.642 --> 2:14:28.852
[exhales] Get used to it.

2:14:31.563 --> 2:14:32.940
Actually...

2:14:35.067 --> 2:14:36.443
there is one thing.

2:14:38.070 --> 2:14:39.321
That brace...

2:14:40.906 --> 2:14:42.950
I've had on all these years...

2:14:44.451 --> 2:14:45.494
when I die...

2:14:47.371 --> 2:14:48.497
I want Charlie...

2:14:49.415 --> 2:14:50.708
to take it out back...

2:14:52.376 --> 2:14:53.711
and shoot it.

2:14:55.254 --> 2:14:57.047
Can you make sure
he does that for me?

2:14:57.047 --> 2:14:58.173
Of course I can.

2:14:59.174 --> 2:15:00.175
[exhales]

2:15:05.222 --> 2:15:08.350
I will see you on the other side
of the mountain.

2:15:10.602 --> 2:15:12.479
See you on the other side
of the mountain.

2:15:24.867 --> 2:15:25.826
[gun cocks]

2:15:37.504 --> 2:15:38.714
[gunshot]

2:15:49.058 --> 2:15:50.225
[Gloria] On election night,

2:15:50.768 --> 2:15:53.896
I was sitting with a group of
female ambassadors to the UN.

2:15:54.646 --> 2:15:56.023
Women from different continents

2:15:56.023 --> 2:15:57.983
who are watching
the results in New York.

2:15:58.734 --> 2:16:00.986
I could see from the faces
around me

2:16:01.487 --> 2:16:03.405
that her defeat
was devastating,

2:16:03.822 --> 2:16:06.617
not just in this country,
but worldwide.

2:16:07.868 --> 2:16:10.037
-[keys clicking]
-Yet I know that in the future,

2:16:10.329 --> 2:16:12.873
Hillary's loss will be part
of our victories.

2:16:13.874 --> 2:16:17.127
Because the path up
is always a jagged line.

2:16:17.586 --> 2:16:18.796
Not a straight one.

2:16:19.546 --> 2:16:22.257
Our victory is not a one
person marathon,

2:16:22.800 --> 2:16:23.926
but a relay race.

2:16:25.010 --> 2:16:27.513
When the first
of many diverse women

2:16:27.513 --> 2:16:30.766
wins this highest
of all democratic offices,

2:16:31.308 --> 2:16:33.977
she'll be climbing steps
that were carved out

2:16:33.977 --> 2:16:35.396
by a woman before her.

2:16:35.896 --> 2:16:37.439
[engine revving]

2:16:37.439 --> 2:16:39.108
[young Gloria] I feel like
we're going in circles.

2:16:40.025 --> 2:16:42.236
Haven't we passed that sign
ten times?

2:16:42.569 --> 2:16:44.446
A gazillion times.

2:16:51.995 --> 2:16:54.289
[indistinct chatter]

2:17:14.268 --> 2:17:16.478
[crowd] This is what democracy
looks like.

2:17:16.478 --> 2:17:17.938
[woman] Tell me
what democracy looks like.

2:17:18.313 --> 2:17:20.607
[crowd] This is what democracy
looks like.

2:17:21.150 --> 2:17:25.821
I and my beloved co-chairs,
the golden oldies, right?

2:17:26.405 --> 2:17:27.698
Harry Belafonte,

2:17:27.698 --> 2:17:29.366
-Dolores Huerta.
-[crowd cheering]

2:17:29.366 --> 2:17:33.287
We may be the oldest marchers
here today,

2:17:34.037 --> 2:17:38.959
so I've been thinking about
the uses of a long life.

2:17:39.376 --> 2:17:44.006
And one of them is that you
remember when things were worse.

2:17:44.256 --> 2:17:45.174
[crowd cheers]

2:17:45.799 --> 2:17:48.635
Thank you for understanding

2:17:48.635 --> 2:17:53.474
that sometimes we must put our
bodies where our beliefs are.

2:17:54.224 --> 2:17:58.270
Sometimes pressing send
is not enough.

2:18:01.148 --> 2:18:02.483
We are here

2:18:02.483 --> 2:18:05.068
and around the world
for a deep democracy...

2:18:05.068 --> 2:18:07.112
that says
we will not be quiet...

2:18:08.071 --> 2:18:09.740
we will not be controlled...

2:18:11.241 --> 2:18:12.993
we will work for a world

2:18:13.243 --> 2:18:15.704
in which all countries
are connected.

2:18:16.497 --> 2:18:18.624
God may be in the details

2:18:18.624 --> 2:18:20.792
but the goddess
is in connections.

2:18:21.210 --> 2:18:22.961
[cheering]

2:18:23.879 --> 2:18:26.757
We are linked.
We are not ranked.

2:18:27.132 --> 2:18:31.845
We are the people. We have
people power and we will use it.

2:18:31.845 --> 2:18:33.597
[cheering]

2:18:33.597 --> 2:18:38.268
This is the upside
of the downside.

2:18:39.228 --> 2:18:43.690
This is an outpouring of energy
and true democracy

2:18:43.690 --> 2:18:48.237
like I have never seen
in my very long life.

2:18:49.071 --> 2:18:53.617
It is wide in age,
it is deep in diversity,

2:18:54.201 --> 2:18:56.286
and remember, the constitution

2:18:56.286 --> 2:18:58.413
does not begin with
"I the president,"

2:18:58.413 --> 2:18:59.540
It begins with,

2:18:59.831 --> 2:19:02.501
-"We the people."
-[crowd] We the people!

